frameDefinitions: A Fuel, some flammable object or substance, ends up on fire.
This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
This frame characterizes the situation or state of affairs in which someone acts to prevent a Fire_disaster from occurring, accelerating, or affecting any area not identified as a Controlled_area.
An Agent changes a Patient's ability to resist literal or figurative attack.
A Fire burns Fuel, resulting in damage and possibly complete destruction of the Fuel.
Using Evidence, which may or may not be expressed, a Cognizer recognizes or proves that Concept1 is associated causally or collocationally with another concept, Concept2.
frameExamples: Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
We <t>bulwarked</t> the castle against the oncoming horde.
A fire that started on Saturday afternoon, the High Glade Fire - located on the Mendocino National Forest's Upper Lake Ranger District - continued to <t>burn</t> actively on Sunday.
